==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pouter
<hw>Pout"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, pouts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. E. <ets>pout</ets>, and G. <ets>puter</ets>
turkey.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A variety of the domestic pigeon
remarkable for the extent to which it is able to dilate its throat and
breast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pouting</ent>⟦br⟧
